1.SPOF: Terminating SSL at the load balancer, this will result vulnarability in data theft.
2.Having only one MySQL server capable of accepting writes is an issue, because if this MySQL server were to fail, all the data changes from the writes would be lost.
3.All servers are configured on a single server, having such configuration will result an issue on security, performance and scalability


